{"id": 231957382, "title": "Cyprus battered by storms, heat grips coast", "text": "Thunderstorms and hail are lashing parts of Cyprus on Sunday, with a yellow warning for heavy rainfall in place until 6:00 PM. Images and videos of the weather event have flooded social media, contrasting sharply with the sweltering temperatures plaguing coastal areas and the capital, Nicosia. A spokesperson for the Department of Meteorology told philenews that data from various stations indicates significant thunderstorm activity. The Saittas station has recorded 16 millimetres of rain, translating to a heavy downpour of 5.5 litres of water per cubic meter per 10 minutes. The Eptagonia station has also seen 9 millimetres of rainfall. The spokesperson added that further storms are expected, potentially affecting inland areas as well. The intense weather is credited with clearing dust from the atmosphere, but officials warn the current instability is temporary. Sunny skies and rising temperatures are forecast for tomorrow, with highs expected to reach 40 degrees Celsius by Tuesday.", "summary": "Thunderstorms and hail are lashing parts of Cyprus on Sunday, with a yellow warning for heavy rainfall in place until 6:00 PM. Images and videos of the weather event have flooded social media, contrasting sharply with the sweltering temperatures plaguing coastal areas and the capital, Nicosia. A spokesperson for the Department of Meteorology told philenews [&#8230;]", "url": "https://in-cyprus.philenews.com/local/cyprus-battered-by-storms-heat-grips-coast/", "image": "https://in-cyprus.philenews.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/xalazi-pic-pagos.jpg", "video": null, "publish_date": "2024-06-09 12:57:11", "author": "newsroom", "authors": ["newsroom"], "language": "en", "source_country": "cy", "sentiment": 0.251}